&lt;p&gt;A winter morning, blinds cracked just enough to send a blade of light raking across a newly painted wall. You step closer. What looked perfect last night is now a relief map—slight ridges at the seams, a faint swirl near an inside corner, a shallow shadow where a butt joint telegraphs through. Every drywall finisher knows this moment. Light exposes the reality of surface prep. The good news: this is controllable. With the right abrasive progression and an efficient joint compound sanding workflow, you can make that same morning light your best QC tool, not your enemy.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/15.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/13/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding/cards/facebook/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/13/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding/cards/facebook/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/13/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding/cards/facebook/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/13/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding/cards/instagram/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/13/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding/cards/instagram/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/13/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-compound-sanding/cards/instagram/best-grit-for-sanding-joint-compound-seams-joint-